  "prompt": "I scored 570 in neet 2 . What would be my expected rank, in total from neet 1 & 2?",
  "response": "To estimate your expected rank in NEET based on a score of 570, we need to consider a few factors:\n\n1. **Total Number of Test Takers**: The total number of candidates who appeared for NEET in both sessions (NEET 1 and NEET 2 combined).\n2. **Difficulty Level**: The relative difficulty of the exams in both sessions.\n3. **Previous Year's Data**: Data from previous years can give us an idea, but keep in mind that each year's competition can vary.\n\nAssuming around 2 million candidates appeared for NEET in total across both sessions (this number can vary year by year), and using data from previous years as a rough guide, here's a general estimation:\n\n- A score of around 570 typically falls in the range where candidates might expect an All India Rank (AIR) somewhere between 50,000 to 70,000. However, this is a very rough estimate.\n\nTo get a more precise estimate, you would need to wait for the official results and the rank list from the National Testing Agency (NTA), as they will provide the actual percentile and rank based on the performance of all candidates.\n\nAlso, consider that the normalization process used by NTA might affect final scores and ranks, especially since you're combining results from two different sessions.\n\nKeep an eye on the official NTA website for the results and subsequent rank announcements. Once the results are out, you can check your exact rank and percentile, which will give you a better idea of your standing and prospects for admission.",
